%% Title: ZinharCMS Backend Request Lifecycle
%% Source evidence: backend/src/main.rs; backend/src/routes/mod.rs; backend/src/middleware/auth.rs; backend/src/middleware/tenant.rs; backend/src/error.rs
%% Related documentation: ../request-handling.md; ../error-handling.md; ../persistence-access.md
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Global as Global Tower Layers
    participant Router as Axum Router Group
    participant Auth as Auth or Tenant Middleware
    participant Handler as Route Handler
    participant Service as Service or Plugin Logic
    participant PostgreSQL
    participant SideEffects as Redis, Files, Providers, or Preview
    participant ErrorMap as AppError Response Mapping

    Client->>Global: HTTP request
    Global->>Router: Apply transport policy and route matching
    alt Public route
        Router->>Handler: Extract public request context
    else Authenticated route
        Router->>Auth: Run authentication middleware
        Auth->>Handler: Attach verified Claims
    else Tenant-protected route
        Router->>Auth: Run tenant middleware and cross-cutting checks
        Auth->>Handler: Attach Claims and TenantContext
    end

    Handler->>Handler: Validate module-specific input and policy
    opt Reusable logic is required
        Handler->>Service: Invoke service or built-in plugin
        opt Service-owned persistence is required
            Service->>PostgreSQL: Execute service-owned SQL
            PostgreSQL-->>Service: Rows or persistence error
        end
        opt Service-owned integration is required
            Service->>SideEffects: Provider, cache, file, webhook, audit, or preview action
            SideEffects-->>Service: Result or infrastructure error
        end
        Service-->>Handler: Service result
    end
    opt Handler-owned persistence is required
        Handler->>PostgreSQL: Execute SQL directly or begin transaction
        PostgreSQL-->>Handler: Rows or persistence error
    end
    opt Handler-owned cross-system side effect is required
        Handler->>SideEffects: Cache, file, provider, webhook, audit, or preview action
        SideEffects-->>Handler: Result or infrastructure error
    end

    alt Successful operation
        Handler-->>Global: Typed Axum response
    else Application failure
        Handler->>ErrorMap: Return AppError
        ErrorMap-->>Global: Status and JSON ErrorBody
    end
    Global-->>Client: Response with request tracing context
